eCurv, Inc. Key Developments

eCurv Introduces Constellation's Efficiency Made Easy Program
Sep 29 15
eCurv reported that it will offer Constellation's Efficiency Made Easy (EME) program to commercial clients. The program provides customers the opportunity to fund the installation of eCurv's QPAC (Queued Power Access) software as part of their Constellation electricity supply agreement. Modeled after the digital queuing technology that has enabled the exponential growth in the service capacity of the Mobile Wireless and Information Technology sectors, eCurv's QPAC service automatically queues the access of electric loads, such as HVAC systems, electric pumps, motors, battery charging, heating and refrigeration equipment, thereby avoiding expensive peak demand events. As part of its Efficiency Made Easy program, Constellation commercial and industrial electricity supply customers are able to implement energy efficiency upgrades and other energy management solutions without up-front capital expenditures.


REGEN Energy Inc. Files Patent Infringement Lawsuit against eCurv Inc
Sep 8 15
REGEN Energy Inc. announced it has filed a patent infringement lawsuit against eCurv Inc., in relation to two of REGEN's core demand management patents. The complaint, filed August 19, 2015 in the U.S. District Court for the Southern District of California, alleges that eCurv's products infringe upon two of REGEN's patents: U.S. Patent No. 8,918,223 and 9,110,647. In the complaint REGEN seeks monetary damages for infringement and a permanent injunction against further infringement by eCurv.


